parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Jumping Out of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jumping out of gear can cause a sudden loss of acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when passing other vehicles or climbing steep grades.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
such as when passing another vehicle or going over a hill; the transmission jumps out of gear
resulting in a sudden loss of acceleration; the transmission grinds or makes a noise when shifting; the vehicle goes into neutral unexpectedly; false neutral between gears.
